{
  "texts": [
    "However, the model is not necessarily tuned for a specific downstream task of interest.",
    "• Task-specific fine-tuning uses domain-specific text data and tunes the parameters of the transformer model while training it for a given downstream task of interest.",
    "One advantage of the first approach is that it can be performed in an unsupervised fashion, i.e.",
    "it does not require labelled data.",
    "Also, the fine-tuned model can be used on different downstream tasks in the same domain."
  ]
}